00:35:45.650 --> 00:35:47.760
And then actually
at the gala event

00:35:47.760 --> 00:35:49.540
where they give
the awards, we were

00:35:49.540 --> 00:35:52.340
sitting at the head table with
Francis Ford Coppola and Angelo

00:35:52.340 --> 00:35:53.240
Gaja.

00:35:53.240 --> 00:35:56.610
And I was saying to my
dad, 20 years ago-- I mean,

00:35:56.610 --> 00:35:59.110
there is no way I
would have predicted

00:35:59.110 --> 00:36:00.450
sitting on this table.

00:36:00.450 --> 00:36:02.800
We almost felt like
cheats or fakes,

00:36:02.800 --> 00:36:05.039
that we were actually sitting
in that table with all

00:36:05.039 --> 00:36:05.580
these people.

00:36:05.580 --> 00:36:08.180
Because we would have
never pictured being there

00:36:08.180 --> 00:36:10.100
or getting there.

00:36:10.100 --> 00:36:12.910
So this book, "Vino
Argentino," and the reason I

00:36:12.910 --> 00:36:14.510
wrote this book
was because I got

00:36:14.510 --> 00:36:16.755
tired of going to taste
things and I'd ask people,

00:36:16.755 --> 00:36:19.440
well when do you think
Argentina started making wine?

00:36:19.440 --> 00:36:21.230
And they'd say 20 years ago.

00:36:21.230 --> 00:36:22.910
And we've been making
wine in Argentina

00:36:22.910 --> 00:36:24.600
since the 16th century.

00:36:24.600 --> 00:36:26.790
We are the fifth largest
of wine in the world.

00:36:26.790 --> 00:36:29.330
We have all these Italian
and Spanish immigrants

00:36:29.330 --> 00:36:31.030
that came to Argentina.

00:36:31.030 --> 00:36:33.510
We drink wine the way
the Italians, the French,

00:36:33.510 --> 00:36:34.850
the Spanish, now the Americans.

00:36:34.850 --> 00:36:38.750
Actually, America keeps on
moving up in wine consumption.

00:36:38.750 --> 00:36:40.570
So this book has a
lot of information

00:36:40.570 --> 00:36:41.880
about the wine country.

00:36:41.880 --> 00:36:42.960
There are some recipes.

00:36:42.960 --> 00:36:44.750
It also has a chapter
on Buenos Aires,

00:36:44.750 --> 00:36:46.430
which restaurants to go to.

00:36:46.430 --> 00:36:47.590
So I hope that you get it.

00:36:47.590 --> 00:36:50.150
And you have a really
cheap price, by the way.

00:36:50.150 --> 00:36:52.390
Because it's normally
sold for $25.

00:36:52.390 --> 00:36:54.472
And apparently there's
a Google discount.

00:36:54.472 --> 00:36:55.430
And you get it for $10.

00:36:55.430 --> 00:36:59.380
I-- actually, my author
copies cost me $11.

00:36:59.380 --> 00:37:03.120
So you have a really good deal.

00:37:03.120 --> 00:37:07.960
So just to review the principles
that we live by at Catena.

00:37:07.960 --> 00:37:09.520
Compete with the best.

00:37:09.520 --> 00:37:11.550
We always aspire
to make wines that

00:37:11.550 --> 00:37:15.250
stand with the
best of the world.

00:37:15.250 --> 00:37:17.220
The academic-- if you
don't know something,

00:37:17.220 --> 00:37:20.367
study it, research it, be
humble about what you know

00:37:20.367 --> 00:37:22.700
and what you don't know.

00:37:22.700 --> 00:37:24.460
Believe and make others believe.

00:37:24.460 --> 00:37:26.320
Sometimes I'll tell
people at the winery,

00:37:26.320 --> 00:37:29.160
find the Elena
Cartena in you, when

00:37:29.160 --> 00:37:31.280
I think they need some guts.

00:37:31.280 --> 00:37:32.780
And home is where the heart is.

00:37:32.780 --> 00:37:35.460
That's a little more
of a personal note.

00:37:35.460 --> 00:37:38.940
When I studied medicine,
I had this idea

00:37:38.940 --> 00:37:40.699
that business people
were bad, that I

00:37:40.699 --> 00:37:42.740
was going to be a doctor
because that was the way

00:37:42.740 --> 00:37:43.740
to help people.

00:37:43.740 --> 00:37:46.150
And sorry, because you
work for a business.

00:37:46.150 --> 00:37:47.690
But I changed my mind.

00:37:47.690 --> 00:37:50.000
And once I started
working with my dad

00:37:50.000 --> 00:37:53.050
and I saw how the rural
communities were changing

00:37:53.050 --> 00:37:57.530
because of wine, how people
now had gardens and had better

00:37:57.530 --> 00:37:59.090
schools and had more wealth.

00:37:59.090 --> 00:38:01.870
And also watching the people
I work, our winemakers,

00:38:01.870 --> 00:38:04.840
who are so inspired
by our daily work

00:38:04.840 --> 00:38:07.260
to make these great
Argentine wines,

00:38:07.260 --> 00:38:08.850
I actually came
to the realization

00:38:08.850 --> 00:38:12.050
that I have a much bigger
impact on the world

00:38:12.050 --> 00:38:13.320
through my wine region.

00:38:13.320 --> 00:38:15.330
And actually, the
work my father has

00:38:15.330 --> 00:38:17.260
done in promoting the
whole region, not just

00:38:17.260 --> 00:38:21.600
our own winery, that is probably
a lot more significant in terms

00:38:21.600 --> 00:38:25.280
of a contribution that
what I do as a physician.

00:38:25.280 --> 00:38:27.470
And so I have kind
of full circle

00:38:27.470 --> 00:38:29.870
changed my mind
about how one can

00:38:29.870 --> 00:38:33.620
make a contribution
to this world.

00:38:33.620 --> 00:38:36.720
And this is just some of the
work that our foundation does.

00:38:36.720 --> 00:38:40.460
It's named after-- that's
my grandmother, Angelica.

00:38:40.460 --> 00:38:42.430
We support some of
the-- we're almost done,

00:38:42.430 --> 00:38:44.030
guys-- three more slides.

00:38:44.030 --> 00:38:50.040
We support some of the local
schools, some of the trade

00:38:50.040 --> 00:38:51.800
schools, because
we feel it's very

00:38:51.800 --> 00:38:53.810
important for the
traditional trades

00:38:53.810 --> 00:38:56.170
to be maintained
in the countryside.

00:38:56.170 --> 00:38:59.790
This is our head of research who
we sponsored to go to UC Davis

00:38:59.790 --> 00:39:01.310
to study.

00:39:01.310 --> 00:39:03.090
And this is our pyramid.

00:39:03.090 --> 00:39:04.930
And the last slide.

00:39:04.930 --> 00:39:07.980
So why we have a pyramid
on all our labels--

00:39:07.980 --> 00:39:11.020
when my father was moving
the vineyards to the higher

00:39:11.020 --> 00:39:14.040
altitude, he wanted to find
an architectural style that

00:39:14.040 --> 00:39:16.190
would symbolize South America.

00:39:16.190 --> 00:39:19.520
And so he didn't want to
make an Italian, or French,

00:39:19.520 --> 00:39:21.470
or a Spanish style building.

00:39:21.470 --> 00:39:23.630
And he was inspired
by the Mayans, who

00:39:23.630 --> 00:39:26.100
were the most advanced
civilization of the Americas

00:39:26.100 --> 00:39:30.840
in terms of astronomy, and
language, and mathematics.

00:39:30.840 --> 00:39:36.670
And so he designed the winery in
the shape of the Mayan pyramid.

00:39:36.670 --> 00:39:39.100
So thank you very much.

00:39:39.100 --> 00:39:40.150
Any questions?

00:39:40.150 --> 00:39:40.650
OK.

00:39:40.650 --> 00:39:42.630
Well, thank you.

