Any other questions?

00:43:13.050 --> 00:43:15.440
AUDIENCE: I was curious how
you feel about your winery's

00:43:15.440 --> 00:43:18.230
interaction with say Wine
Spectator or other critics who

00:43:18.230 --> 00:43:21.489
seem to fairly carefully control
who is successful and was not?

00:43:21.489 --> 00:43:22.280
LAURA CATENA: Yeah.

00:43:22.280 --> 00:43:25.930
So this is a big question in
wine about the wine critics.

00:43:25.930 --> 00:43:28.190
And some people think
they have too much power.

00:43:28.190 --> 00:43:31.540
Some people criticize
their kind of palates.

00:43:31.540 --> 00:43:34.180
Some other people think
you can buy ratings.

00:43:34.180 --> 00:43:37.670
Well, I can tell you for sure
that if you could buy ratings,

00:43:37.670 --> 00:43:39.850
I would have been the first
one to try to buy one.

00:43:39.850 --> 00:43:42.010
Sorry, but you can't.

00:43:42.010 --> 00:43:43.030
You can't buy ratings.

00:43:43.030 --> 00:43:44.300
You send your wines.

00:43:44.300 --> 00:43:45.510
They taste them blind.

00:43:45.510 --> 00:43:48.570
And I know people that
work at these magazines.

00:43:48.570 --> 00:43:51.260
And they said it is
completely blind.

00:43:51.260 --> 00:43:58.271
So it's-- I don't know why some
wines get rated higher than

00:43:58.271 --> 00:43:58.770
others.

00:43:58.770 --> 00:44:00.050
Hopefully it's the quality.

00:44:00.050 --> 00:44:03.950
I do think that some reviewers
have certain palates.

00:44:03.950 --> 00:44:06.460
And so you might do better
with a certain style.

00:44:06.460 --> 00:44:09.440
But I don't think, like many
people say Robert Parker likes

00:44:09.440 --> 00:44:11.230
huge oaky wines,
and I've actually

00:44:11.230 --> 00:44:13.290
seen him review
highly some wines that

00:44:13.290 --> 00:44:15.320
are very elegant and delicate.

00:44:15.320 --> 00:44:21.870
So my view is there's--
consumers like ratings.

00:44:21.870 --> 00:44:25.940
And for me as a
developing country,

00:44:25.940 --> 00:44:29.330
I would have had a hard
time proving to anybody

00:44:29.330 --> 00:44:32.170
that my wine was good
without these ratings.

00:44:32.170 --> 00:44:34.990
So for us, they've
worked really well.

00:44:34.990 --> 00:44:36.940
Does it seem unfair sometimes?

00:44:36.940 --> 00:44:38.472
I'll taste a really great wine.

00:44:38.472 --> 00:44:39.930
And it doesn't have
a great review.

00:44:39.930 --> 00:44:41.304
And I feel like,
wow this I would

00:44:41.304 --> 00:44:43.670
have given this wine 95 points.

00:44:43.670 --> 00:44:45.390
And it got 85.

00:44:45.390 --> 00:44:49.220
And if I were that wine
maker, I'd be pretty sad.

00:44:49.220 --> 00:44:53.530
But for us, it's given
us this opportunity

00:44:53.530 --> 00:44:55.610
to compete with the first world.

00:44:55.610 --> 00:45:01.020
So-- and I can tell you that
these people are totally legit.

00:45:01.020 --> 00:45:04.490
You cannot buy a score.

00:45:04.490 --> 00:45:05.950
You send your wine.

00:45:05.950 --> 00:45:06.800
They review it.

00:45:06.800 --> 00:45:08.680
And we've got mostly
great reviews.

00:45:08.680 --> 00:45:11.260
But we had a few bad reviews.

00:45:11.260 --> 00:45:18.176
And my dad sends us all
kinds of emails when we do.

00:45:18.176 --> 00:45:20.550
But thank you for that question,
very important question.

00:45:20.550 --> 00:45:20.710
Yeah.

00:45:20.710 --> 00:45:23.260
But in the end, I think you
should follow your own palate.

00:45:23.260 --> 00:45:24.760
If you taste a wine
and you love it,

00:45:24.760 --> 00:45:28.270
obviously ignore whatever
the reviewer said.

00:45:28.270 --> 00:45:31.470
But if you find a reviewer
that shares your palate.

00:45:31.470 --> 00:45:35.440
If you find that they generally
rate highly wines that you

00:45:35.440 --> 00:45:37.620
like, then you might
want to follow them.

00:45:37.620 --> 00:45:38.780
Especially if it's my wine.

