00:46:38.870 --> 00:46:40.911
And I'm wondering if that
has to do with the fact

00:46:40.911 --> 00:46:44.170
that what you're experiencing
is the taste of the winemaker,

00:46:44.170 --> 00:46:46.850
rather than the actual
purity of the varietal.

00:46:46.850 --> 00:46:48.910
LAURA CATENA: That is
just an awesome question.

00:46:48.910 --> 00:46:50.840
It's almost a half hour answer.

00:46:50.840 --> 00:46:52.890
But I won't do a half hour.

00:46:52.890 --> 00:46:56.680
So you can do blends within
a vineyard of different lots.

00:46:56.680 --> 00:46:59.920
You can do altitude blend, which
is what the Catena Malbec is.

00:46:59.920 --> 00:47:01.860
You can do blends
of many varieties.

00:47:01.860 --> 00:47:04.570
So for example, in
many parts of France,

00:47:04.570 --> 00:47:07.430
you're only allowed to
plant certain varieties.

00:47:07.430 --> 00:47:10.049
So in Bordeaux, you can
only find five varieties.

00:47:10.049 --> 00:47:11.590
And every wine from
Bordeaux is going

00:47:11.590 --> 00:47:15.100
to be a blend of one
or five of those.

00:47:15.100 --> 00:47:18.210
I think that traditional
blends like Bordeaux, people

00:47:18.210 --> 00:47:21.030
spend 400 years planting
these different varieties

00:47:21.030 --> 00:47:23.150
and figuring out what goes well.

00:47:23.150 --> 00:47:25.680
So generally, a blend
is going to be a wine

00:47:25.680 --> 00:47:28.100
that's very balanced
and that makes sense.

00:47:28.100 --> 00:47:31.380
Because somebody spent a lot
of time making that wine.

00:47:31.380 --> 00:47:35.770
And it might be a little
more elegant and smooth.

00:47:35.770 --> 00:47:38.300
Sometimes though, it's fun to
try a single vineyard wine.

00:47:38.300 --> 00:47:39.800
And you'll taste
the Adrianna, where

00:47:39.800 --> 00:47:41.460
you get a little edginess.

00:47:41.460 --> 00:47:45.140
And maybe it's not that perfect
of a wine, or not that smooth,

00:47:45.140 --> 00:47:47.134
but it has a very
distinctive style.

00:47:47.134 --> 00:47:48.550
So it's almost
like the difference

00:47:48.550 --> 00:47:50.610
between wearing something
that looks really good

00:47:50.610 --> 00:47:52.130
and wearing something crazy.

00:47:52.130 --> 00:47:53.520
Both are good.

00:47:53.520 --> 00:47:55.540
But it depends on what you like.

00:47:55.540 --> 00:47:59.870
And I do think that in blends,
the winemaker's palate is key.

00:47:59.870 --> 00:48:02.540
And one of things I tell
people about a family winery

00:48:02.540 --> 00:48:05.390
is that the only
guarantee I can give you

00:48:05.390 --> 00:48:07.660
is that my father and
I taste all the wines.

00:48:07.660 --> 00:48:10.090
And we like to
drink what we make.

00:48:10.090 --> 00:48:12.780
But I can't tell you the my wine
is better than my neighbor's.

00:48:12.780 --> 00:48:16.550
I can only tell you that I
am making a wine that I like.

00:48:16.550 --> 00:48:17.117
Yeah.

00:48:17.117 --> 00:48:17.950
Thank you very much.

00:48:17.950 --> 00:48:18.850
Gracias.

00:48:18.850 --> 00:48:20.400
[APPLAUSE]

